 archives of the New York Times Company and civil rights leaders, Samantha Barbas tracks the saga behind one of the most important First Amendment rulings in history. She situates the case within the turbulent 1960s and the history of the press, alongside striking portraits of the lawyers, officials, judges, activists, editors, and journalists who brought and defended the case. As the Sullivan doctrine faces growing controversy, Actual Malice reminds us of the stakes of the case that shaped American reporting and public discourse as we know it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh  a1960s.  aArthur Hays Sulzberger.  aJustice William Brennan.  acivil rights movement.  aconstitutional law.  adefamation.  afirst amendment.  afree speech law.  ajournalism history.  alibel law.  anews media.  anewspaper.  apress freedom.  asupreme court opinion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520385832?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520385832423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520385832/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY